    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-29T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-29T07:00:00-05:00" n="10"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/522: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winship</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-29T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 29, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 29—7:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Department’s telegram 9, April 27.<note n="26" xml:id="d10fn26">See last
                        paragraph of telegram No. 8, April 27, 6 p.m., to the Minister in Sweden,
                            <ref target="#pg_9">p. 9</ref>.</note> Danish Government in sympathy
                    with convention national defense expenditures made public <pb facs="0023" n="11"
                        xml:id="pg_11"/> annually in defense budget regarding control and publicity
                    of arms manufacture and sale, see my despatch No. 565, October 23, 1936.<note
                        n="27" xml:id="d10fn27">Not printed.</note> Parliament now debating new
                    Government bill extending control similar to law recently enacted in Sweden.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winship</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
